Responder
LLMNR/NBT-NS/MDNS poisoner and credential harvester

Sniffing & Spoofing
Description
Responder is a tool that poisons LLMNR, NBT-NS, and MDNS queries on a network, capturing NTLMv1/v2 hashes from victims. It's used for internal network penetration testing.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which responder
Install command:

sudo apt install responder
Basic Syntax
responder -I <interface> [options]
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
responder -I eth0

Basic poisoning	Start capturing hashes on network	
responder -I eth0 -wrf

Full attack mode	Enable WPAD, fingerprinting	
responder -I eth0 -A

Analyze mode	Passive analysis without poisoning	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Connect to target network
2
